name: Womens Flashbomb Heatseeker 4/3mm Zip Free Wetsuit
description:
The new Women's Flashbomb Heat Seeker 4/3 fullsuit is our most technically advanced cold water wetsuit to date. This suit combines all new E7 Flash Lining through out, and our unique Version 2 Flex Energy lining that generates even more heat when stretched. Plus many more superior technical features, the Flashbomb Heat Seeker is our warmest and most flexible Flashbomb ever.

THE DETAILS:
Mesh Skin Chest Panel
E7 Flash Lining
Hand Taped
Flex Energy
Single Seam Crutch
Unbroken Panel

E7 FLASH-LINING - 100% E7 Flash Lining that is exclusive to Rip Curl. It has an incredible 20% more stretch than E6 Flash Lining. Further improved drying properties for ultimate warmth and comfort.

FLEX ENERGY - A revolutionary lining on the back and shoulders that generates heat when stretched. As you move through the water, the Flex Energy lining will activate and hear your wetsuits. Stay active, stay warm.

SINGLE SEAM CRUTCH - No seam to sit on and increased stretch.

UNBROKEN PANEL - Back and shoulder, to maximise paddle efficiency and ease of movement.

name: Womens Furno Warmth 4/3mm Chest Zip Wetsuit
description:
Get a FREE Nyord hanger when you buy a Nyord wetsuit. Produced in the UK using 100% recycled ocean plastics.

Perfect for you if: You’re a regular surfer who needs a wetsuit you can wear mid-spring all the way through to autumn.

Balancing comfort and warmth with flexibility, Nyord's mid-price wetsuit is a great all-rounder. The super-stretchy limestone neoprene, combined with a plush internal lining on the chest and back, retains heat without restricting movement. Glued and blind stitched seams, as well as strong taping on key areas of wear, provide a watertight and durable seal. The Glideskin neck and anti-slip ankle and wrist cuffs prevent water from flushing your suit.

THE DETAILS:
Super-stretch Limestone Neoprene - Derived from limestone, Nyord's super-stretch neoprene delivers great flexibility and reduces our reliance on oil by replacing traditional petroleum-based neoprene.
Thermolokker Lining - A soft brushed thermal lining with 4-way stretch. Large loops in the fabric trap heat for great thermal insulation.
Supersilke Seam Tape - A durable, high stretch taping is used to reinforce key areas of wear and eliminate leaks.
Glideskin Neck - Glideskin is a very stretchy and comfortable type of neoprene. It sits snugly against the skin to prevent flushing.
GBS Seams - Panel edges are glued together and stitched on the inside. The neoprene is only partially perforated, resulting in a watertight and flexible seam.
Anti-slip Ankle & Wrist Cuffs - Anti-slip cuffs stay put for a more comfortable fit and create a watertight seal to prevent flushing.
YKK Chest Zip
MATERIALS:
Limestone neoprene
Supersilke taping on key seams
Thermolokker lining (chest and back)
Glideskin neoprene neck

name: Womens Dazzled 4/3mm Back Zip Wetsuit
description:

All seams are glued blind stitched and have critical taping added to the most vulnerable seams around the waist.

THE DETAILS:
Waterproof stretch taping (50%): critical areas - A neoprene taping is positioned on the critical seams of the suit. This prevents water from coming through the seams on critical points of the human body.
GBS (Glued Blind Stitched) - Stitching method whereby the panels are first glued together and then only stitched halfway through the fabric instead of fully perforating it, which makes the seams waterproof.
YKK Back-zip
Glideskin neck construction
Overhead backup shield
Hex-tech kneepads

Non slip cuffs
Key pocket 2.0: keyloop with mini buckle - An external neoprene key pocket conveniently positioned on the lower leg of the suit. The standard key loop is now equipped with a mini-buckle to release your key with ease while making sure your key is safe inside.
Aquaflush - Wipe out or simply needed to take a leak? The perforated neoprene patches on the lower leg, that we like to call Aquaflush, will ensure that all liquids exit the suit easily.
MATERIALS:
M-Flex (100%) - Now you've decided you're getting a kick out of the cold and wind, why not upgrade to M-Flex 100%? It'll keep you warm and also provides more stretch. Get ready for your next step and prepare well for the conditions you're about to face.
Fox fleece in chest, back and lower body - Big loops in the fabric create a high pile lining that holds air for extra insulation. It holds less water enhancing the fast-drying abilities of the fabric. With its superior stretch performance in all directions it’s super suitable for every panel in all of our suit.

GBS (Glued Blind Stitched)

TECHNOLOGY:
Waterproof stretch taping critical areas - A highly durable taping is used in the crucial areas of the suit to avoid leaking and keep it flexible and warm.
Glued blind stitching is a method whereby the panels are first glued together and then only stitched halfway through the fabric instead of fully perforating it, which makes the seams waterproof.
Wind mesh has closed cell neoprene with one side of fabric lamination. The outside of the mesh neoprene offers a better protection against wind chill.
Aquabarrier - This is a silicone printing on the collarbone region of your wetsuit. This forms a barrier between the overlapping front-zip panels preventing water from entering.
Key pocket 2.0 - A key loop with mini buckle - An external neoprene key pocket conveniently positioned on the lower leg of the suit. The standard key loop is now equipped with a mini-buckle to release your key with ease while making sure your key is safe inside.

name: Womens Diva 4/3 Double Chest Zip Wetsuit
description:
The sickest graphics backed by the newest technologies. A great combo of performance and style. The DIVA is designed for those who dare to be out there and comes in the colorful Aurora or Black & White allover print. The front-zip provides more flex in the upper body, giving you that extra freedom of movement. On the inside the DIVA has fully waterproof stretch taped seams combined with Flaremesh on the back and chest panels. The rest of the torso panels have Fox Fleece lining to ensure maximum comfort and warmth.

Form and function, anything else?

Fine Mystic front zip - The fine overlapping teeth create a smooth and tight closure, while maintaining the flexible capabilities of the suit. The strong metal puller with the rubber fingergrip enables an easy handling.

Windmesh chest & back panel - Eliminates windchilland keeps you warmer for longer.
GBS (glued and blindstitched) - Strong & flexible seams.
Hex-tech knee pads - Ultra durable & flexible knee pads.
Key pocket 2.0 - Keyloop with mini-buckle.
Aquaflush - Perforated neoprene that allows water to exit the suit, preventing the leg cuffs from filling up with water.
Velcro ankle closure straps - Velcro ankle straps to tighten the leg cuffs.
Aquabarrier - Silicone printing which forms a barrier, preventing water from entering your suit.
Non slip cuffs - The cuff is designed to limit the water entry and keep the sleeve in place.
M-Flex 2.0 100% - The most flexible neoprene in our range. M-Flex 2.0 updated with even better stretch and flex properties.
Flaremesh internal lining in chest, back, lower body & hood - High performance inner lining with excellent stretch & heat reflection.
Fox Fleece internally in all other panels - Soft, smooth & incredibly warm.
Waterproof stretch taping internally - Stops water ingress through the seams.

Fox Fleece:

Soft, smooth and incredibly warm, the renewed thermal inner lining called Fox Fleece has big loops in the fabric create a high pile lining that holds air for extra insulation. The fleece also holds less water enhancing the fast-drying abilities of the fabric. Fox Fleece has superior stretch performance in all directions making it super suitable for every panel in all of our suits.

Flaremesh:

Flaremesh lining has a carbon backing and is topped with big terry loops creating a high pile for extra insulation and a soft touch. Flaremesh also channels water through the fabric to decrease drying time. This finally puts and end to sessions starting with a wet and cold suit. The jacquard knit design is unique to Mystic’s wetsuits.
